<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<assessmentItem xmlns="http://www.imsglobal.org/xsd/imsqti_v2p0"
    xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance"
    xsi:schemaLocation="http://www.imsglobal.org/xsd/imsqti_v2p0
    http://www.imsglobal.org/xsd/imsqti_v2p0.xsd" identifier="T007.05" title="Test 7.05 Table
    Elements" adaptive="false" timeDependent="false">
    <stylesheet href="tableElements.css" type="text/css"/>
    <itemBody>
        <p>This test uses scope and headers attributes to indicate the relationship between some
            of the cells.  It also uses the axis attribute to identify the diagonal cells
            and the abbr attribute to provide abbreviated forms of each header cell.  Systems
            are not required to use any of these, though for systems that support CSS the
            diagonal elements should be placed on a red background.</p>
        <table>
            <tbody>
                <tr>
                    <th></th>
                    <th scope="col" abbr="1">Col 1</th>
                    <th id="c2" abbr="2">Col 2</th>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <th id="rA" abbr="A">Row A</th>
                    <td axis="diagonal">A1</td>
                    <td headers="rA c2">A2</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <th abbr="B">Row B</th>
                    <td>B1</td>
                    <td axis="diagonal">B2</td>
                </tr>
            </tbody>
        </table>
    </itemBody>
</assessmentItem>
